<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raid Leader:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Vulrath<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Secondary Raid Leader:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Shabba<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Time:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Saturday, January 11th at 12:00 Noon EST – sometime in the evening<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Objective:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> To clear the plane as much as possible and take down the 2-3 Golems, Wraith of Shissar (if up) and Dracoliche. I will call the raid when we achieve these objectives or loose too many people to continue.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Groups:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I will be taking up to 10 full groups. No more. If you have LD problems usually, you might want to stay home on this one – Fear raids are usually pretty big.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Classes/Levels:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Raid will be restricted to levels <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>48</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and above. Evils are welcome.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Channels</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Main raid channel – fvfear<br>
Raid Chat channel – fvfearchat<br>
Debuff channel – fvfeardebuff<br>
Help Me channel – fvfearhelp<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sign-up:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Please sign up on this post including your level and class and any other information you feel I need to know (I.E. coming late, leaving early etc.). Preference will be shown in the sign-up according to the following: 1. WoA member, 2. Fellowship member, 3. Class, 4. Level. These preferences will be given up to 2 days before the raid begins. After noon on the 9th of January, all other spots will be filled on a FCFS basis if there are any left open so sign up early and edit your post if you gain levels. I will post a list of people signed up and going 2 days before so check back as this raid approaches.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Meeting location:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> We will be meeting in The Feerott in front of the portal to Fear at 11:30AM. Please be there early with Anon/RP off and LFG on and ready to go as soon as possible. DON’T send me a tell at 12:00 saying, “Hold on, I’m in Cobalt Scar, I’ll be right there!” You can find a map for The Feerott  with a drawing of the cave system here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/feerottmap.html">www.eqatlas.com/feerottmap.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
There are specters in the cave so please announce it if you will be training them to the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maps:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Here are a couple maps of Fear:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/fearplane2.jpg">www.eqmaps.com/m3/fearplane2.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/fearplane4.jpg">www.eqmaps.com/m3/fearplane4.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
The first one shows the two camps (west and north and the second one is a good accurate picture of the plane.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Loot:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Please read this carefully so there are no uncertainties.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> There are 2 epic pieces reserved - the first Shaman Epic Tear for me and the Broken Golem for the Wizard epic for Ephraim. The Wizard epic creature was added because a turn-in is required. I went from the top of the list down for those requesting it. Jaranna was first to ask but can no longer go. Ephraim was next. If Ephraim can't go, it will go to the next Wizard who asked and is ready. All other epic pieces will be randomed on the spot between the people needing them. All other gear loot will be randomed NBG at the end of the raid so please plan on staying the full time. At the end, I will do the randoms on large-class-spectrum items (All/All etc) first and Class-specific gear second. If you win a piece of gear, you will not be allowed to roll again until all members of your class have gotten a piece. <br>
The only people doing the looting on this raid will be the group leaders. If you aren’t a group leader and start looting, you will receive a warning (see below). Randoms will be 0-1000. I will allow the following people to add 100 points to a roll of their choice but they have to specify it before the roll: the CoTH mage if we do a CoTH break-in and each “sacrifice” to eat the first DT from a golem. These will be the only preferences given for loot. NBG status for each item at the end will be determined by me and is not open for discussion. If I say an item is for casters only, I don’t want Hybrids asking me to roll on it. If the raid goes well we will all have a selection of items to roll on.<br>
All money loot (coin, jewelry, gems etc.) will be saved until the end of the raid and turned in to me. At that point, reimbursements will be taken out for components and the remaining items will be split among those who didn’t receive a piece of gear.<br>
Loot fights are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not acceptable</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and are cause for removal from the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Components:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> All priests and buffers, please be responsible for your components – only use them when appropriate, and keep track of expenditures. At the end of the raid, notify your group leader of total expense and I will take it out of any money loot gained (if we have enough) and return it to you. If we do a CoTH break in, I will supply the pearls and take the cost out of the money loot at the end of the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Warnings:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I work on a 3 strike system. You will receive a warning for bad raid behavior (not listening, breaking mez, training, arguing, being stupid etc.). If you receive 3 strikes you are given a TL out with no opportunity for loot. I am pretty calm about things, but if someone is being an ass and annoying me and the entire raid or if someone is doing things that are dangerous to the raid, I will not tolerate that. If you have doubts about raid behavior please read my post:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=3211.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...3211.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Break-In:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> We will do a 3 group break in to start the raid – basically I will assemble 3 groups full of high levels and AOEers. We will enter invised and run to the West Wall camp. We will then AOE kill anything that aggroed us on the journey. Then we will clear a safe path from the portal to the wall and I will send up the next groups one by one to run to the West Wall camp. If this goes right, break-in should only take about 30 mins.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>AOE clearing:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ok, we will be set up for an AOE clear of the plane. If you are not familiar with how this works, this is what will happen. Many of the casting classes can AOE – point blank AOE is most effective because there is no target limit. Rain AOEs and others are also nice but the damage is usually limited to a certain number of targets. We will have all the classes that can Point Blank AOE load these spells and all other classes that can AOE but not Point Blank load those spells. A fully buffed tank will run out in the middle of the zone and grab a large train of things. They run around and group them together so there is a large mass of things chasing them. Then the run them back to the “kill zone” – the area just in front of the raid. They then stop and let all the things catch up and take a couple seconds of beatings – then all the enchanters in the raid AOE stun everything. No mezzes – just stuns. All other classes that can stun can make sure anything that resisted is stunned and anything that comes late is stunned once it hits the group of creatures. Once everything is stunned – the Wizards and all other Point Blank AOE classes wade into the center of the creatures and begin to AOE – when this begins, all other classes with AOEs can fire them and melee classes wade in and help out. After a short bit, everything dies or is near dead and we repeat the process. We will be giving direction on the raid so if you don’t understand this, it will be repeated. I will enlist the help of Ephraim who has done this before and hopefully will help coordinate this.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Grouping:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Groups will be made according to the PoP raid function. If you don’t have PoP yet, I will put you into a separate non-PoP group. All commands will go to the main chat channel so non-PoPers won’t be left out. <br>
<br>
Notices have been sent out to all of the larger guilds on FV of our intent to raid Fear on this date. I have requested that they leave the mini-bosses up from 1/8 to 1/11 so hopefully we will get a clear shot at the plane.<br>
<br>
The following people are confirmed for this raid. Please continue to edit your posts if you gain levels or can't attend. If you are listed as a reserve, please consider yourself going. No raid in the history of EQ has ever had perfect attendence of people signed up so more than likely you will be going.<br>
